---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="movement | human nature health"
  description="movement as a natural part of human wellbeing."
>
  <section class="page-hero section">
    <div class="container narrow">
      <p class="eyebrow">movement</p>
      <h1>the body wants to be used, not parked.</h1>
      <p class="lead">
        movement supports circulation, posture, energy, mood, resilience, and a stronger connection
        to your own body.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container narrow">
      <div class="content-block">
        <h2>why movement matters</h2>
        <p>
          the human body responds well to motion. when people stop moving enough, energy drops,
          stiffness rises, posture weakens, and stress tends to build.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="content-block">
        <h2>what often goes wrong</h2>
        <p>
          too much sitting, too little walking, poor posture, and treating exercise like punishment
          instead of nourishment can make movement feel harder than it needs to.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="content-block">
        <h2>core principles</h2>
        <div class="content-list">
          <p>walk often</p>
          <p>train strength regularly</p>
          <p>stretch and stay mobile</p>
          <p>spend more time outside</p>
          <p>think of movement as daily life, not just workouts</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section accent-section">
    <div class="container narrow">
      <h2>a simple movement rhythm</h2>

      <div class="content-block">
        <h3>morning</h3>
        <p>
          a short walk, a little mobility, or even just moving your body early helps shift the day
          in the right direction.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="content-block">
        <h3>day</h3>
        <p>
          break up long periods of sitting. walk, stand, stretch, and use the body in smaller
          repeated ways.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="content-block">
        <h3>week</h3>
        <p>
          include some form of strength training, steady walking, and mobility so the body stays
          capable and responsive.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container narrow">
      <div class="quote-block">
        <p>
          movement is one of the body’s main languages. the more you ignore it, the worse life tends to feel.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container narrow">
      <div class="y2k-panel feature-card">
        <div class="panel-heading-row">
          <p class="panel-kicker">checklist</p>
          <span class="panel-stamp">movement</span>
        </div>
        <h2>simple movement checklist</h2>
        <div class="content-list">
          <p>walk daily (20–60 min total)</p>
          <p>strength train 2–4x per week</p>
          <p>break up long sitting every 30–60 min</p>
          <p>include mobility or stretching</p>
          <p>spend time moving outdoors</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container narrow">
      <div class="two-panel-grid">
        <a href="/sunlight" class="y2k-panel feature-card">
          <p class="panel-kicker">previous</p>
          <h3>sunlight</h3>
          <p>return to light, rhythm, and daily energy.</p>
        </a>

        <a href="/nervous-system" class="y2k-panel feature-card">
          <p class="panel-kicker">next</p>
          <h3>nervous system</h3>
          <p>continue into calming the body and regulating stress.</p>
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>